F] AIM: Write a JSP program that demonstrates the use of JSP declaration, scriptlet, directives, 
expression, header and footer. 
CODE:  
header.jsp 
<%@ page language="java" %> 
22 
 
<html><head><title>JSP Demo</title></head> 
<body><hr><h2 align="center">Welcome to JSP Demo Page</h2><hr> 
 
footer.jsp 
<hr><footer> <p>&copy; 2025 JSP Demo Application</p></footer></body></html> 
mainIndex.jsp 
<%@ page language="java" contentType="text/html" %> 
<%@ include file="header.jsp" %> 
<%-- JSP Declaration --%> 
<%! int a = 10; int b = 20  
    int add() { return a + b; }%> 
<%-- JSP Scriptlet --%> 
<% String name = "Student"; 
    int result = add(); %> 
<h3>JSP Elements Demonstration</h3> 
<%-- JSP Expression --%> 
<p>Name: <%= name %></p> 
<p>Addition Result: <%= result %></p> 
<p>Current Date & Time: <%= new java.util.Date() %></p> 
<%@ include file="footer.jsp" %>
